[master 5671a6ce] fix(nav): preserve blog post slug when switching language\n\nUser feedback #2798: clicking a language switcher in the nav while\non a /blog/<slug> page jumped back to /<locale>/blog list, losing\nthe article. /notes/<slug> was already correct (kept the slug).\n\nRoot cause in src/components/layout/Navbar.tsx getLocalePath():\n  // Blog post slugs are per-locale, so redirect to new locale's blog list\n  if (pathPart.startsWith('/blog/')) return /blogList  (in target locale)\n  return /<targetLocale><pathPart>\n\nThe hardcoded "blog post - list" branch was based on a wrong\nassumption. The blog uses the same slug filenames across all three\nlocales (Frank translates manually, so /ja/posts/why-i-left-china-\nfor-japan.mdx, /zh/posts/...mdx, /en/posts/...mdx all share the\nfilename). Notes already worked because that branch never existed\nfor /notes/.\n\nFix: delete the blog branch. /blog/<slug> now falls through to the\ngeneric return /<targetLocale><pathPart>, exactly like /notes/<slug>.\n\nAll ASCII on purpose (Cloudflare Pages API strict-UTF-8 issue).
